Emoji Mood Changer

A simple and fun web project where you can cycle through different emojis to express various moods by clicking a button. Built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, it’s perfect for beginners to practice DOM manipulation, event handling, and styling.

Features

Click the “Change Mood” button to cycle through a variety of emojis.

Emoji container is centered on the page.

Background image behind the container for a visually appealing design.

Fully responsive and easy to customize.

Demo


(Replace with your actual screenshot)

Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/your-username/emoji-mood-changer.git


Open index.html in your favorite browser.

Usage

Open the page in a browser.

Click the “Change Mood” button.

Watch the emoji update and cycle through different moods!

File Structure
emoji-mood-changer/
│
├── index.html       # Main HTML file
├── css/
│   └── style.css    # Styles for container, background, and button
└── js/
    └── index.js     # JavaScript for emoji cycling functionality

Customization

Add or remove emojis: Edit the emojis array in index.js.

Change background image: Update the background-image URL in style.css.

Adjust container size: Modify width and height in .emoji-container CSS.

Technologies Used

HTML5

CSS3 (Flexbox, Backgrounds)

JavaScript (DOM manipulation, Event listeners)

